  "description": "The first Contra game for the 32-bit consoles and released exactly 10 years after the <a href=\"https://www.mobygames.com/game/contra\">first Contra</a>.<br><br>Unlike the original Contra and follow-ups, this is an overhead-view 2D shooter (with 3D graphics) that plays more like a side-scrolling <a href=\"https://www.mobygames.com/search/quick?game=Commando\">Commando</a> or <a href=\"https://www.mobygames.com/search/quick?game=Mercs\">Mercs</a>.<br><br>The graphics are truly 3D; an option allows you to view them as red/blue images, and some packages of Contra: LoW come with 3D glasses to garner full enjoyment of the feature.<br><br>Hidden within the game – accessible on a certain level and through a secret code – are a mini-version of <a href=\"https://www.mobygames.com/game/gyruss\">Gyruss</a> and a <a href=\"https://www.mobygames.com/search/quick?gamegroup=Pac-Man+Variants\">Pac-Man-like</a> game called Pactank.",
